## 1. Product Vision

**ArbWatch** watches a trader's BSC token shortlist for real price gaps between PancakeSwap and Binance, has an AI agent sanity-check whether the gap survives fees and slippage, and only acts after the human approves — connecting their own wallet, importing their own tokens, and (in simulated mode for today) executing the trade end to end with a logged, explainable outcome.

The pitch to judges: this is not a black-box autotrader. It's a transparent decision pipeline — deterministic math where math is correct, AI judgment where judgment is needed, and a human in the loop wherever real consequences exist. That's a more credible, more fundable story than "fully autonomous bot," and it's also literally how Lemma is designed to be used (Functions for rules, Agents for judgment, Approvals for consequence).

---

## 2. Problem Statement

A trader watching a handful of BSC tokens has no fast way to know, at any moment, whether PancakeSwap and Binance have drifted apart enough to be worth acting on — and even when a gap shows up, eyeballing a raw percentage doesn't tell you if it survives PancakeSwap's swap fee, Binance's trading fee, slippage on a thin pool, and BSC gas. Most "spreads" people see on dashboards are not actually profitable once real costs are counted. ArbWatch automates both the watching and the costing, and stops short of pulling the trigger without a human saying yes.

---

## 3. Users & Use Case

**Primary user:** a self-directed crypto trader (you) running a personal shortlist of 5–15 BSC tokens, who wants pre-costed, pre-judged alerts instead of raw spread numbers, and wants to connect their own wallet rather than hand custody to a bot.

**Core scenario:** open the app → connect wallet → paste in a new token to track → the system scans on a schedule or on demand → a signal shows up with a plain-English read on whether it's real → approve → see the (simulated, for today) trade result logged with actual numbers.

